opicID=26.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A bit of a suprise...</span><hr size=1> Mojo held his battle axe in rediment as Hades seemed to 'Rant' at him.  He growled slightly at the sight of Hades.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Oh and why is it you 'let' me escape oh Mighty Hades?&quot; he ramarked in a sarcatic and condecending tone.  &quot;I'm not afraid you of you.  Not even when I was a child did I fear you.  Nor do I now, nor will I EVER!  So approaching me and talking down to me like this won't help you.  Only makes me lose respect for you.  And if you are wondering why I avoided you in the Underworld, it is due to the fact that, I pick and choose my battles.  A battle with you at that point in time would not have benefited me.&quot;<br>
<br>
His growling tone seemed to dull a bit at the appearance of Tisiphone.  He remembered his brief encounter with the Furies when he was young.  The three sisters were impossible to forget once seen again.  He even remembers feeling their presense, though not visibly, on some of the battlefields he fought.  He noded a bit and smiled.  He had a strong feeling she was here as an ally and not an enemy.  He put his axe on the leather hanger that slung to his back.  He bowed slightly to Tisiphone and then very slowly and very gently touched her cheek, as a silent 'Thank You' for intervening on his behalf before Hades. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/16/01 12:52:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A bit of a suprise...</span><hr size=1> Hades stood there folding his arms.  &quot;Well Mojo, it seems you have a few allies to your side.&quot;  He nods respectably to both Tisiphone and Hypnos.  <br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not here to ridicule the minotaur.  I'm only here to REMIND him.  I also don't want his head swelling up.  An you're right Hypnos.  He has 'earned' it.&quot;  <br>
<br>
He then pats Mojo on his massive shoulder before stepping back on folding his arms again, and a wry grin playing upon his face.  <br>
<br>
&quot;And you are right, he has not cheated his destiny.  Thus is the reason I allowed him to leave.  He still has things to do&quot;. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A> at: 4/16/01 12:56:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/16/01 1:10:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> She smiled softly, she of course did not remember encountering him before. She went through a period in her life where she had forgotten much due to her intake of pain from the mortals she had to torture. <br>
<br>
As he touched her cheek she pulled back slightly almost in shock. But to her amazement, he felt no pain when he touched her. Not many were able to overcome that. But he apparently was. She then calmed down and smiled once again nodding her head towards him.<br>
